Class ArrayListRecordSet<R extends Record>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList<R>
          • org.judal.storage.table.impl.ArrayListRecordSet<R>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<R>, Collection<R>, List<R>, RandomAccess, RecordSet<R>

    public class ArrayListRecordSet<R extends Record>
extends ArrayList<R>
implements RecordSet<R>

    An array representing data read from a database table or view.

    ArrayListRecordSet object is used for reading a collection of registers from the database and keep them in memory for immediate access.

    1.0
